body:
Personally, I believe neither `Assert.Throws<T>` nor `Assert.DoesNotThrow<T>`  should exist:

``` C#
// act
var ex = Record.Exception(() => sut.Foo());

// assert
Assert.IsType<ExpectedException>(ex);
```

or

``` C#
// act
var ex = Record.Exception(() => sut.Foo());

// assert
Assert.Null(ex);
```
